text: Does this look awesome?  Yes.  Will I be watching it? Yes.  Is it Power Rangers? ...no, not really.  It's J.J. Abrams and Star Trek all over again.  Are his movies good?  Yes.  Did I enjoy them?  Yes.  But were they really at all related to the source material?  ...no, not really.  And for Light's sake, can we dispense with the 'gritty reboot' thing already?  Why do the kids all have to be criminals/outcasts/whatever?  Why can't they be just... you know... normal kids?  Like they always have been in damn near every incarnation of Power Rangers ever?  Oh, and I still think the suits make them look like Beetleborgs.  Should have gone with that one, Saban.

text: Okay, here we go. The original Power Rangers was mostly cheesy fighting, childish humor and a lot of toy advertisement, glued together with a certain drive and intensity best showcased by the heavy metal intro. They had to change it up for this movie, no question. But there was more than one way to do it, and apparently they went for underdog-bullying-romance-teenage-drama-shit while showing no understanding for what was awesome about the original series. Instead of a slightly darker but fun and badass approach, this just feels... it feels *whiny*. Like a dumb and whiny movie for dumb and whiny teens. Just like Kingsman. Wow, fuck Kingsman.

text: Ehhhh...I didn't enjoy this at all :(. What's with the epic trailer music, dark colors and tragic characters? was this trailer made by Christopher Nolan? where's the electric guitar riffs and bright, cheesy 90's fun? It looks like they're giving this movie the "Man of Steel" treatment or something ><.   It's POWER RANGERS. It doesn't need to be serious or edgy. It just needs to be fun, and this doesn't feel fun to me. More like they're giving it the Dragon Ball Evolution/Michael Bay TMNT/Every single DC movie since The Dark Knight treatment, and producers doing what they THINK kids want instead of want kids actually want. I mean, I don't know, but judging by the trailer, I wouldn't want to see this movie if I was a kid :/.  Haha, sorry for the rant but...can we have, like, one franchise from our childhood still be fun? what's next: a Mortal Kombat reboot where Liu Kang is struggling in high school? geez, there's enough grittiness watching the freaking election all year. text: This, this is a movie I've been hoping would be made for YEARS.  I will go in as a fan who grew up with MIghty Morphin, Zeo, Turbo(the movie still stings, not in a good way), In Space, Lost Galaxy, Lightspeed Rescue, Time Force, Wild Force, Ninja Storm, Dino Thunder, and Mystic Force to name a few of the seasons I watched.  Overall, I accept this is a new universe creation, and while I hope there is a good amount of proper homage credit given I just hope I reclaim the feeling from the original even for a while.  But if this stings like the Turbo Movie or the Fantastic Four reboot it'll hurt.  Reboots alone aren't bad, but they have to be done right and recognized as reboots that can at least link to source material in some fashion other than name and some very minor character traits.

text: Please to all power ranger fans, please, PLEASE look at this open minded. Looking at it, you think it sucks, cliche, disgrace to its predecessors. That's the problem, its not supposed to be like the originals. Its a new era, things are going to change, so if you complaining saying new stuff sucks, that's just you and others saying it sucks. Hell, you're tricking yourself it sucks JUST BECAUSE IT'S NEW! The only reason this franchise is declining is because of the fans, not just because it "sucks". Yes, the newer ones seem very lack-luster in good acting but it is good in some elements. Im not saying the new stuff is good, but if we the fans start encouraging and stop hating on the franchise, hell they might make a really good fucking movie! But then you'll complain that its new and it sucks, but it doesn't suck and you just want to have the originals back. You infect other people with your opinion, and they start thinking it's shit too. So, please. For the franchise, for what you enjoyed as a child, or as a fan that watched it later in their lives, or people that just like it casually. Don't just assume it sucks, IT HASN'T EVEN COME OUT. Please make this top comment, because I hope even just a few other power ranger fans can look at this and at least consider t an option. And if you TL:DR (Too long: Didn't read), I just hope you know my message.

text: Yes, Rita SHOULD have the Green power coin. The Green candle held the Green Ranger's power, and was evil. She selected Tommy to be the Green Ranger as he and he alone could truly handle the power (the Green Ranger was stronger than the 5 good guy Rangers combined). He ended up siding with the good guys after a bit of time, and stayed as the Green Ranger until the candle burned out and the power went away. Zordon and Alphalpha used what they learned from the Green Ranger's power and made the White Ranger. They brought back Tommy as the White Ranger but had to warn him to be careful, as it was much weaker than the Green Ranger that he was used to, but still as strong as 2-3 of the normal Rangers combined. They did this for balancing, as after they showed the Green Ranger's strength he literally could beat all the normal Rangers+Zordon+Alphalpha quite easily. Hence, Saban made the candle burn out thus leading Tommy to become the much-weaker-yet-still-strong-enough-to-be-the-leader White Ranger lol.  There you guys go. text: So, here is the primary problem; you're forcusing way to fucking heavy on the teen drama. There was a BIT of it, but that's now what it was about. It was about Rita being freed, Zordon creating the rangers out of the five most viable humans from Angel grove. Sentai has it's moments of drama, but it'd played for *laughs* primarily. It's SUPPOSED to be over the top and "bad" in many aspects. When it's serious, it's fucking serious, but when it isn't, it never tries to be. So watching this trailer, what do i see?  I see 5 misfits in a teen drama being bullied be ebul bullies and a split second of them getting suits at the end of the trailer.  nononono FUCKING NO. you give, at most, 30 seconds to the "teen" aspect, then you have shit go down, them become the rangers, and then show off the zords. text: I like where this is going and I see why it's a lot darker than the Power Rangers TV series'. I've only seen one series of Power Rangers (PW: SPD to be specific) and I liked that series, but I understand why this film is going with a darker tone instead of it's usual TV tropes. Ever since Marvel have been running the superhero movie franchise with their darker tones, Power Rangers probably had to go with a similar concept just to reach out to a similar audience.  Hopefully this will be a good adaptation and will rekindle the nostalgia for old fans and peak the interest of new ones. Also for those that complain that it's gonna suck because it's not like the show, this films clearly been made to hit a much larger demographic than just 'Power Rangers Fans', so just wait and see till the movie comes out and actually go into the theater with an unbiased, neutral approach to the film. And if you like it, well done I'm glad you did, and if you didn't like it then fair enough, it's your opinion.

text: Why do I read the comments? I always trash people who stop traffic to see a cop pull someone over when there is nothing to see. Yet, here I am, KNOWING every other comment is going to be negative, trashing a 2 minute trailer as if everyone just is just absolutely an expert and can tell, "this is gonna suck", but I look anyway‚Ä¶when you geniuses have the resources to make your perfect version of what you think a movie should be, then you can trash someone else's. This is one writer's, or group of writer's, idea of how to tell this story. If it doesn't match what you saw when you were 8, oh well. Make your own. If it bombs, someone else will do another one in a few years. Hell, even if does well, it'll get trashed by the masses because it doesn't follow the original in some insane way.... at least this genre of movies is alive and well. What if no one ever took the time to do sci-fi/comic book/superhero movie? We'd have to choose between Brokeback Mountain or The Notebook every weekend. Be thankful people are trying to do these stories‚Ä¶ no one is ever friggin happy...ugh, I hate people

text: Trailer looks great, and hearing the last few bars of the original theme song from the original TV show - bringing back cool memories, I swear !!!!!! I'm a grown friggin' man, but even I can safely say I'm pumped for this. Heck, I might even ask mom if she'd take me to the theaters to see this. (And my prior thinking was - because of the fact that that James Holmes asshole murdering people, it caused me to have a type of phobia of ever wanting to go into ANY theaters (I admit it.). I'm sure security is more bad-ass and tight since that horrible shooting I heard about at the time, but still - can any one person blame me for my phobia of wanting to ever go into anymore theaters anymore ? Considering waiting until it's out on DVD/video to get it. Not sure about the Brian Cranston as Zordon thing, but IF I DO get to see it, I'll give that a chance. I just hope they don't screw it up. The new Ranger SUITS look bad-ass !!!!! I just hope they allow an Asian lady to portray Trini, as sort of a tribute to  the lovely Thuy Trang, who played Trini in the original Rangers, who passed in a vehicle accident, years ago. If the movie payed homage to her, I'll get back to being a Rangers fan, COMPLETELY !!! At the moment, I'm iffy in supporting them for now.

text: The Ode to Rangers.  So long hath it been since mine eyes have been deceived, So long has it been since the days of old. Here I stand with my eyes aglaze, watching and waiting for the return of my days. So long has it been since I've seen so clear, the absolute danger they face in a kind of race against time. The Rangers, the absolute power they hold in their hands to thwart the evil Rita's succulent demands. Yet something is a miss with all that is happened, I see not one speck of those who we held dear in the past. Where oh where are the ones I seek, Alpha five and the awesome Zordon? Hath it been a promise that I made myself? Or lies strewn about in a tangled web like one of Rita's evil lies?  A tangled skein to hold their fates a web of lies to put them in place, I seek those who once we called family. Zordon my father, Aplha my friend, Rita my mother and Zedd is my brother. Goldar and Hog are like my two uncles but I see them not, save who I thought would turn to be Rita, to place the Rangers in a trap more deadly than those of past, will it be or will it not be the time that I see the Rangers at last.  I will forever hold the original series and Rangers in my heart forever. GO GO POWER RANGERS!!! Till the end.

text: Ok i'm conflicted. I grew up with the original power rangers all the way and i truly love those rangers because that was my childhood, it brings back great memories for me and i will always be happy watching those old episodes (yes i'm a dork and i have all the mighty morphin seasons on dvd and i'm trying to get the others i watched too lol). And honestly that nostalgic part of me screamed no when i saw the first few seconds of this, it really did. BUT i have to say if this wasn't associated with the power rangers franchise i would be much more interested in seeing this movie because it honestly looks cool. It is gritty looking for a young adult movie, looks like it works well in todays world and it has super powers, you can't really go wrong with that combination lol. It's just the power ranger part that throws me off and makes me feel unsure. And yes i know people get all mad because they think nostalgia clouds judgement and too a point it does and it always will. It's very hard to look at a new version of something you grew up with. It doesn't matter what genre or era you're from it will always be a little hard to separate those feelings but i do think this will be an interesting film and i hope it does well.

text: I love how people in the comments are acting like the original Power Rangers was like this godsend show. News flash! Take off your nostalgia goggles for a second, stop bitching and realize that it was this dumb thing you liked as a kid. The fight scenes in the original show are just reused footage from a Japanese show called, Zyurangers. The American show just placed these teenagers with bad acting to form a story Americans can understand.  You can dislike this film, you're allowed, but calling this shit while praising the old show and trying to defend it is hilariously laughable.

text: Alright, first up: I don't know what drugs they were on what made them not show at least one scene with them fully suited up, but I get the hype strategy. Secondly, I am VERY optimistic about this movie. I mean, for all the nerdherd-level awesomeness of most every Power Rangers season that's ever walked the face of TV, the whole thing has always been a bit... cheesy. I like the fact that they're taking a more grown-up approach with the visuals, and the plot, really throwing in a backstory that fits well with the "teenagers with an attitude" tagline. At the very least, I'm pretty sure this movie won't completely suck.

text: Now, I remember the original Power Rangers, and I loved them back when I was a kid. What I see is a total revamping of the franchise, while still keeping the entertaining yet cliche elements of the original. Rita seems much more menacing than she did in the TV show, and that's commendable. All things considered, this movie seems to be geared more toward the original Power Rangers fans, being as we're all grown up now, and it seems to have much more...mature themes to it. I HOPE this movie however, does not try to be more than it is- A Power Rangers movie.
